Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) based composite anode with SDC interlayer for solid oxide electrolysis cell was prepared by screen printing technique.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-based Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: Electrochemical performance of the electrode at 800 degrees C was examined by linear sweep voltammetry (LSV) and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) methods.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-based Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: The result of EIS analysis suggestes that the oxidation kinetics of O2- to O-2 is controlled by three electrode procedures, including charge transfer at the electrode/interlayer interface, charge transfer at the interlayer/electrolyte interface and oxygen desorption/diffusion.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-based Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: Scanning electron microscope analysis shows that composite anode layer, SDC interlayer and the electrolyte are integrated and well-combined.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-based Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell

Sentencas: In terms of anode polarization, LSCF based material exhibites a better application perspective rather than traditional LSM-YSZ composite material for SOEC anode.
Titulo: Preparation and Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-based Composite Anode for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cell
